rience is a plus.\nCategory Management IC3 - The typical base pay range for this role across the U.S. is USD $85,100 - $169,800 per year. There is a different range applicable to specific work locations, within the San Francisco Bay area and New York City metropolitan area, and the base pay range for this role in those locations is USD $112,000 - $185,300 per year.\n Find additional benefits and pay information\nhere: https://careers.microsoft.com/us/en/us-corporate-pay \nMicrosoft will accept applications for the role until September 18th, 2025. \nResponsibilities\n General Management\nManage business operations within a category from end-to-end, serving as a subject matter expert on the Americas Accessories Category (e.g., product/service knowledge; historical context; category trends; where a product/service sits within category strategy), and provides expertise on the broader category and industry. \nReport data-driven product channel insights from partners (e.g., voice of the customer [VOC] data) back to the Worldwide Category team and/or the business group to support product strategy, maximize revenue, and help define future product development. \nFinancial Accountability\nManages accountability for top-line and bottom-line profit and loss for the Gaming Accessories category. \nEnsures efficient use of organizational resources to execute marketing and promotional plans within the category. \nManages & support key category management functions in fiscal year forecasting, planning, and budgeting, and ensures financial compliance. \nBusiness Planning & ROB\nSupports the development of go-to-market (GTM) plans and key performance indicators (KPIs) for Americas Accessories Category. Contributes to the definition of execution plans in partnership with key stakeholders (e.g., Sales, Marketing, Finance). Produces a regular cadence of reports as required to track overall performance and identify trends.\nContributes to review meetings as a part of the rhythm of business (ROB) cadence and summarizes feedback on business and campaign performance for a portion of a product or service area.\nIn partnership with key stakeholders (e.g., Sales, Marketing, Finance, Sales Excellence, Business Operations), defines and owns product specific channel strategy and investments, supports development of execution plans, and drives longer-term initiatives for the region. \nExecution\nManages execution of category strategy and investments with partners. Adjusts programs and investments, and ensures alignment of execution plans as needed using guidance from corporate and performance data. \nLeverages financial performance data and models to ensure expected outcomes are delivered, and feeds back market insights to corporate to address competitive concerns within the market. \nMeasuring and Monitoring\nLeverages deep knowledge of analyses and results to be able to simplify data and report results. Translates data analytics into actionable business insights. \nDisseminates insights to ensure that key stakeholders understand the factors driving performance and what course corrections or resources are needed to enable categories to hit their targets. \nShares best practices with internal stakeholders and business partners for identifying trends across the product category. \nLeverages historical analyses and insights to support business planning and provide future projections on trends and impacts. \nBusiness Steward\nSupports reporting on top-line and bottom-line profit and loss for Americas Accessories. Ensures spend optimization for assigned area. Helps ensure that the allocated budget/investment is properly spent and in alignment with business objectives. Understands financial compliance and aligns with compliance rules and regulations, asking questions to build an understanding of compliance.\nContributes to business operations within a portion of a category and/or region, providing product expertise (e.g., market, audience, technical features) for 