ome together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.\n In alignment with our Microsoft values, we are committed to cultivating an inclusive work environment for all employees to positively impact our culture every day.\nQualifications\nRequired Qualifications:\nDoctorate in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or related field AND 5+ years data-science experience (e.g., managing structured and unstructured data, applying statistical techniques and reporting results)\nOR Master's Degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or related field AND 7+ years data-science experience (e.g., managing structured and unstructured data, applying statistical techniques and reporting results)\nOR Bachelor's Degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or related field AND 10+ years data science experience (e.g., managing structured and unstructured data, applying statistical techniques and reporting results)\nOR equivalent experience.\nExperience in managing AND using Azure services such as Power BI, Fabric, Azure Data Explorer, Azure SQL, or third parties equivalent (i.e. Snowflake on Azure) within the last 12 months.\nPreferred Qualifications:\nDoctorate in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or related field AND 8+ years data-science experience (e.g., managing structured and unstructured data, applying statistical techniques and reporting results)\nOR Master's Degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or related field AND 10+ years data-science experience (e.g., managing structured and unstructured data, applying statistical techniques and reporting results)\nOR Bachelor's Degree in Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Econometrics, Economics, Operations Research, Computer Science, or related field AND 12+ years data-science experience (e.g., managing structured and unstructured data, applying statistical techniques and reporting results)\nOR equivalent experience.\nExperience in Microsoft Copilot Studio, AI Foundry and other AI environments as a plus.\nExperience working with large, distributed data sets to derive actional insight.\nAdvanced skills in big data programming language.\n   Data Science IC5 - The typical base pay range for this role across the U.S. is USD $139,900 - $274,800 per year. There is a different range applicable to specific work locations, within the San Francisco Bay area and New York City metropolitan area, and the base pay range for this role in those locations is USD $188,000 - $304,200 per year.\n\nCertain roles may be eligible for benefits and other compensation. Find additional benefits and pay information here: https://careers.microsoft.com/us/en/us-corporate-pay\n\nMicrosoft will accept applications for the role until September 15, 2025.\n Responsibilities\nBusiness understanding and impact. Leverages understanding of data science and business to examine a project and consider factors that can influence final outcomes. Documents key business objectives. Effectively communicates business goals in analytical and technical terms. Consistently shares insights with stakeholders.\nData Engineering. Understands where to acquire data necessary for successful completion of the project plan. Utilizes querying, visualization, and reporting techniques to describe acquired data, including format, quantity, identities, and other surface properties. Collaborates with others to perform data-science experiments using established methodologies, statistics, optimization, and probability theory for general purpose software and statistical packages. Serves as an effective partner in data preparation efforts to Solution Architects and other business stakeholders (Commercial Solution Areas). Adheres to Microsoft's privacy and security policies related to collecting and preparing data. Identifies data integrity problems.\nBusiness Insights Warehouse. Establishes and maintains a scalable data warehouse leveraging Microsoft Fabric and Azure data platforms (Azure Data Explorer, Azure Data Factory, and Databricks) to support data science teams on building data-driven insights, forecasting, propensity modeling, and customer targeting efficiently.\nInfrastructure. Maintain team’s Azure subscription, managing resources to optimize performance inside the available budget. Ensure the data warehouse and involve Azure resources meet security and privacy compliance and AI readiness requirements. Evolve data platform to meet new requirements, including leveraging new Microsoft technologies, with the objective of improving productivity and showcasing the latest Microsoft innovations.\nBusiness and Research Knowledge/Opportunity Identification. Learns and understands the current state of the Commercials Solution Areas business, including knowledge of tools, techniques, strategies, and processes that can be utilized to improve process efficiency and performance. Maintains knowledge of current trends within the discipline.\nBusiness Insights AI Innovation. Leveraging the latest technology, drive an innovation agenda, integrating AI to transform insights delivery.\nOther:\nBe a hands-on technical lead who can own, drive, and develop data platform from conception to release.\nBe curious and willing to continuously learn about the business; partner with stakeholders to define the critical insights required to make informed business decisions and sales precision.\nContinuously evolve the output of this role and ensure business alignment and impact. Be motivated by learni