ise across Microsoft and non-Microsoft cloud-based technologies.  \n Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.\nQualifications\nRequired Qualifications (RQs)\n7+ years Data technical pre-sales or Data Modernization technical consulting experience\nOR bachelor’s degree in computer science, Information Technology, or related field AND 6+ years Data & Analytics technical pre-sales or Data Modernization technical consulting experience\nOR master’s degree in computer science, Information Technology, or related field AND 4+ years technical Data & Analytics pre-sales or technical consulting experience\nOR equivalent experience\n Preferred Qualifications (PQs)\nSpanish and English fluency\n8+ years technical pre-sales, technical consulting, or technology delivery, or related experience\nPartners: Experience leveraging partner solutions to solve customer needs and scale opportunities.\nProof of Concepts: Experience creating Data Modernization, Analytics and AI Proof of Concepts (PoC)/Pilots for customers that lead to production deployments. \nOR equivalent experience\n6+ years’ experience with Data Modernization & Analytics cloud and hybrid, or on premises infrastructures, Data architecture designs, Data & Analytics migrations, industry standards, and/or Data Modernization technology management\nCertification in relevant technologies or disciplines (e.g., Data Modernization, Analytics and Database Architect and Development exams, Data Cloud Platform Technologies).\n  Responsibilities\nOwn Data Modernization & AI technical discussions with customers leveraging processes and tools, demos, and programs using consultative sales methodology and technical expertise to influence the customer vision; establish rules of engagement (e.g., role boundaries, handoff strategies) for extended teams.\nBuild Data Modernization technical strategy: map the agreed customer vision into a strategy, resolve concerns, preventing and removing technical blockers, and validating a strong business case for investment and translating technology complexity into business impact.  Work with the customer, account team, and partners to orchestrate a roadmap for implementation guiding the customer to choose the best Microsoft platform and win the AI Design, inclusive of Microsoft AI, Application services, and Databases. \nLead and design the solution using your Data & AI technical knowledge, architectural approach, consultancy skills and our methodology to win a customer’s technical decision and meet the customer’s needs; drive POCs/Pilots to create momentum for MVPs, infusing key Data modernization and AI technologies where appropriate and being technically proficient to do POC with hands-on-skills.\nCross collaboration across AI, and Apps Innovation team to drive AI Design Wins and support the customer AI transformation inclusive of AI Applications and data foundation. Support the creation of new pipeline in collaboration with the Specialist and account team by identifying new opportunities within customer engagement and hand-off to the Solution Specialist for pursuit.\nMaintain and grow expertise in Database scenarios including Cosmos DB, SQL DB, and PostgreSQL as well as relevant AI technologies while keeping up to date with market trends and competitive insights; collaborate and share with the Data & AI technical community.\nBe the Trusted advisor and use proactive effort to find and understand customers’ pain points and work with partners to design and offer solutions (with business case) to technical leaders by being an Azure platform evangelist for Database scenarios like modernizing your legacy Data Warehouse and migrating to the