rd shipping AI solutions to production.\nLLMOps/MLOps at scale including experiment tracking, CI/CD for models, automated evaluations, A/B or canary releases, and quality/drift monitoring (e.g., MLflow, Kubeflow, Weights & Biases).\nSafety, security & governance for AI systems: red‑teaming, prompt‑injection/Jailbreak defenses, PII handling, policy/guardrails, and auditability.\nStrong development background in programming languages such as .NET, Python, Java, or JavaScript/Node.js, with proven experience in cloud-native and microservices architectures.\nThorough understanding of the full Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) with deep knowledge of DevSecOps practices and proven experience implementing them at scale\nStrong expertise in containerization platforms like Kubernetes, Docker and Azure Container Apps.\nTechnical Certification in Cloud (e.g., Azure, Amazon Web Services, Google, security certifications)\n Responsibilities\nAs a Cloud Solution Architect in the Cloud + AI Apps team your responsibilities will include:\nBuild trusted relationships with IT Executives and business leaders to shape their Cloud and AI strategy, acting as a technical advisor and champion for their success.\nLead architectural design sessions and guide the implementation of secure, scalable, and resilient solutions using Microsoft’s best practices and frameworks like CAF and WAF.\nDrive technical excellence across Azure workloads—including AI, Apps, and Data—ensuring mission-critical workloads are optimized for performance, security, and production-scale AI readiness.\nOwn the end-to-end technical delivery for a defined set of strategic accounts, ensuring alignment with customer success plans and maximizing the value of Microsoft investments.\nAccelerate Azure consumption and customer outcomes by delivering repeatable IP, resolving technical blockers, and providing delivery oversight for key engagements.\nCollaborate with internal teams and partners to design impactful delivery proposals and support execution with clarity and confidence.\nActively contribute to Microsoft’s technical communities by mentoring peers, sharing insights, and serving as a spokesperson in internal and external forums.\nStay ahead of the curve by maintaining advanced certifications and deep technical expertise across priority workloads such as Azure AI Foundry, GitHub, App Services, Databricks, Fabric, and more.\nInspire customer innovation by helping them adopt AI at scale, guiding them through their transformation journey with confidence and clarity.\nDemonstrate a growth mindset by continuously developing your skills, aligning with business priorities, and contributing to a culture of learning and excellence.",
